✡️ 2. The Divine Name

In Hebrew, writing the full Tetragrammaton (יהוה) on jewelry is avoided out of reverence, but the letters or a partial form—like יה or שדי (Shaddai)—are common protective inscriptions.

“שדי” has even been found on ancient amulets and mezuzah cases.

That makes it both historically and spiritually appropriate for a design that honors divine protection without crossing sacred boundaries.

